metadata.name: Petri 1500 #724
metadata.description:
Petri 1500 is a celebration of reaching 1500 Twitter followers.
As I've grown as an artist what represents that growth but a petri dish, filled with life, finding a way. 

A sillybration of all things fx(hash) featuring some of my recognisable pallets and primatives
along with something new to me - noise and 'realistic' nature sketches. 
All mashed for pure fun.

L to download 1000x1000
S to download 4000x4000

metadata.name: ____ - Iteration 1 #472
metadata.description:
This project is part of a larger experiment that explores and celebrates the process of making generative art by progressively releasing iterations, working towards a final release on my main account (tz1RkYY3jr1ocuPdQqrRefr5FqoawKQsmBmD). The iterations will be titled ____ 0.1, ____ 0.2, etc. At this point, the number of iterations has not been determined, but more information will be provided as this experiment unfolds.

The final release will only be made available to those who have collected each iteration (using an allowlist), and will be released for free.

metadata.name: Match and Connect #90
metadata.description:
Connect side by side object with matching shape or color inside a grid system.

one line one color for matching color
one line with two colors for matching shape
three line for matching shape and color

Variations:
13 palettes;
Earthquake mode; (rare)
Change size mode; (rare)
Just stroke mode; (rare)
Frame mode; (rare)

created using p5js
